# 🚀 Hero Section — Version 2.0 Major UI Redesign

The **Hero Section** ([HeroSection.jsx](file:///e:/DELTA/M%20A%20I%20N%20M%20A%20I%20N/FULL%20STACK%20DEPLOYES%20PROJECTS/Job%20finding%20MERN%20application/frontend/src/components/home/HeroSection.jsx)) has been completely redesigned to match the high-end *Version 2.0* aesthetics. It now acts as an interactive, immersive entry point for the application.

## ✅ Features Implemented

| Feature | Status |
|---------|--------|
| **Interactive Glassmorphism Search** | ✅ *Search bar expands and glows with accent colors when focused.* |
| **Parallax Mouse-Tracking Orbs** | ✅ *Background gradient orbs elegantly follow mouse movements.* |
| **Sequential Text Reveal** | ✅ *Headline words animate upwards in a staggered sequence.* |
| **Floating 3D-like Badges** | ✅ *Stats like "10K+ Hired" float continuously with CSS keyframes.* |
| **Avatar Stack (Social Proof)** | ✅ *Overlapping user profile pictures with a neat hover expansion.* |
| **Animated Stat Cards** | ✅ *Hover reveals a rotating conic-gradient border effect.* |
| **Gradient Call-to-Action** | ✅ *The "Search" button features an internal sliding gradient on hover.* |
| **Subtle Grid Background** | ✅ *A faded radial-masked grid adds depth to both Light and Dark modes.* |
| **Version Update Chip** | ✅ *A glowing "v2.0 UI Overhaul Live" badge at the top of the header.* |
| **High Performance** | ✅ *Relies strictly on CSS transforms/opacity and minimal React state.* |

## 🚀 Performance & UX Highlights
- **Zero JS Animation Overhead**: Staggered animations are done using inline `animation-delay` on pure CSS keyframes (`wordFadeUp`).
- **Immersive Feedback**: The search bar physically reacts (`scale(1.02)` + dynamic shadow/border colors) based on the user's cursor focus, creating a highly tactile experience.
- **Mouse Tracking**: The parallax background orbs map to the mouse coordinates (`clientX`/`clientY`) via CSS custom properties, ensuring 60FPS smoothness without causing React re-renders.
- **Thematic Consistency**: The gradients (`Purple`→`Pink`→`Orange`) and typography match the exact tokens used in the new Navbar and Auth pages.

